Seq2.ReceiverContent: Sure, one moment, let me show you to Brandy and she could help you out with this. Please stay online.

Seq3.CallerContent: Hi Brandy, this is Daniel Nunez. You called me yesterday.

Seq4.CallerContent: Okay, yeah, correct. The photo ID and the medical insurance is in there as well because it said to send photo ID.
Seq4.ReceiverContent: Oh yeah, Mr. Nunez, I talked to you about sending your insurance. I saw it that it was sent in. I haven't opened an email though, I just scanned over them.

Seq6.CallerContent: Okay, and I just have one more question about the patient portal. I've never set up the patient portal, and then I tried setting it up yesterday, and, I don't know, it was being a little weird.
Seq6.ReceiverContent: Yeah, unfortunately what I can do is I'll go into your chart and make sure that you're web enabled. It should be, though, because you have an appointment coming up this afternoon.

Seq7.ReceiverContent: Yeah, but give me a little bit, and I'll give you a call back. I can guarantee you that, sir.

Seq8.ReceiverContent: No problem, Mr. Nunez. Thank you for calling in this morning, and you have a great afternoon.
